Key Publications & Research
Text Summarization Tool: Applications and Results
This publication explores the development and practical applications of a text summarization tool. It delves into the methodologies used to condense large volumes of text into concise summaries, highlighting its effectiveness across various domains and presenting the measurable results achieved.
Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG): How AI Grounds Itself in Fact
This research paper provides an in-depth analysis of Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), a crucial technique in modern AI. It explains how RAG enables AI models to retrieve information from external knowledge bases, thereby grounding their responses in factual data and significantly reducing hallucinations in generative AI outputs.
